Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharp turn. Clay fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp with ribboned thyrsus(?) symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Polyaratos. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0399.07.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1051)
